Jack Costanzo & Gerry Woo - Jive Samba\\nAA. Al Escobar & His Orchestra - Tighten Up\\n\\nA. Jack Costanzo & Gerry Woo - Jive Samba\\n\\nJack ‘Mr Bongo’ Costanzo - the man that spawned the name for our label nonetheless! American born bandleader, composer, conducter and dancer nicknamed Mr Bongo for popularising the instrument.\\n\\nCostanzo played with Peggy Lee, Perez Prado, Frank Sinatra and many many more. Clearly a friend of the stars, he taught the likes of Marlon Brando, Betty Gable and Carolyn Jones to play bongo’s.\\n\\n‘Jive Samba’ is taken from his ‘Latin Percussion With Soul’ album recorded with Gerry Woo, released on Tico in 1968.\\n\\n Previously unreleased on 7”.\\n\\n \\n\\nAA.
